main event: A farmer in South Wellington, Texas spotted an oval-shaped object about 20 inches in diameter that was emitting a low-level hum. The object was first seen hovering about 30 feet from the ground, then it moved off at a high rate of speed.
interesting points: The object was described as having a white light with a 'fluttery' quality when parked, and the light turned reddish when the object began to move.
Drawings of the object and its interior compartment were obtained.
The observer was described as a reliable and stable individual who has lived in the area his whole life, except for one year.
There were multiple sightings of similar objects reported in the area.
The conclusive findings and cause of the sighting were undetermined.
sighted object: oval-shaped object about 20 inches in diameter, emitting a low-level hum
